subSubSection.paragraph:
Gonopods (
Figs 9–13
, 
22–24
) in anterior view (
Fig. 9
) with flattened, plate-like anterior angiocoxites, sharply bent posteriad at a transverse ridge about midway in angiocoxite length, proximal to ridge are a few low rugae. In lateral view (
Fig. 11
), tip of anterior angiocoxite (
Figs 12, 13
, 
23, 24
) with complex array of sharply curved, acute spinules, subterminal spine sharply bent at tip, abruptly becoming acute. Posterior angiocoxites sheathing three or four flagellocoxites (
Fig. 10
), with subterminal hook-like process, three terminal divisions. Ninth legs typical, median coxal process small, weak.
